The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, January 10, 2004 				 Kalpana 
 New Delhi, Jan. 9: Astronaut  Kalpana Chawla was posthumously awarded the Pravasi Bharatiya  Samman Puraskar along with 11 others by the Prime Minister  today, reports our special correspondent.																								She epitomised the values that are so laudable in overseas Indians. A daughter of India, she became an exemplary citizen of the US and went on to become a citizen of the universe. Her journey from Karnal to Cosmos will continue to inspire young Indians  indeed, young people all over the world, A.B. Vajpayee said as he handed over the award to her husband Jean Pierre Harrison.																								The gathering at the Pravasi Bharatiya Divas gave Chawla a standing ovation. 
